<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A120925379BFF4BC56DFCF2" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" type="description">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A120925379BFF4BC7C2FF1E" blockId="2.[151,572,151,214]" box="[151,410,187,214]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A120925379BFF4BC75BFF1D" box="[151,259,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Figs. 4–6</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A1209253602FF4BC7CEFF1E" box="[270,406,187,214]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–32" captionStartId="6.[151,264,958,982]" captionTargetBox="[294,1289,187,930]" captionTargetId="figure-18@6.[292,1295,181,934]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 25–32. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov. 25. Male pygofer side, lateral view; 26. Valve, ventral view; 27. Subgenital plates, ventral view; 28. Aedeagus, ventral view; 29. Apex of aedeagus, dorsal view; 30. Aedeagus, lateral view; 31. Connective, ventral view; 32. Style, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501263" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501263/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Figs. 25–32</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A0436850A120925379BFEF3C272FE42" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A120925379BFEF3C771FED5" bold="true" box="[151,297,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Description.</emphasis>
Color pattern of anterior dorsum and face as in 
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A120925346DFEF3C597FED5" box="[865,975,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Figs. 1–4</figureCitation>
. Body brown. Crown with four circular markings. Eyes black, ocelli yellow. Pronotum anterior yellowish-brown with some black and yellow markings, posterior brown. Scutellum brown, with some yellow markings. Face pale yellow with brown transverse markings; anteclypeus and lorum yellow. Forewing yellowish-brown, with many dark spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A0436850A12092537CBFE63C6B0FDF5" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Head in dorsal view slightly narrower than pronotum. Eyes large, ocelli on anterior margin. Face flattened. Anteclypeus broadening apically. Pronotum anterior margin strongly and roundly produced, posterior margin straight. Scutellum triangular, longer than median length of pronotum, with transverse suture. Forewing with four apical cells and three subapical cells, appendix small. Hind femur broadened distally and slightly bowed, apical setal formula 2+2+1.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3A0436850A12092537CBFDB7C7DCFCDD" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A12092537CBFDB7C72CFDA9" box="[199,372,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer side narrow towards posterior margin with stout setae; posterior with a long line process, curved ventrally (
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A12092536ACFD9BC7BEFD4E" box="[416,486,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Valve triangular (
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A12092535C8FD9BC552FD4E" box="[708,778,619,646]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate broad basally, tapered over distal, with eight long setae and some macrosetae along lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A1209253447FD7FC5CAFD62" box="[843,914,655,682]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft thin with two pairs of small processes in ventral view and with a abdominal process lateral view; gonopore apical (
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A1209253379FD43C2BCFD05" box="[1141,1252,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Figs. 8, 9</figureCitation>
). Connective Yshaped, stem slightly thinner than arms (
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A1209253564FD27C4E5FD39" box="[616,701,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Style broad at base, abruptly narrowing subapically with some macrosetae (
<figureCitation id="A2802A000A1209253628FD0BC72EFCDD" box="[292,374,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1909,1933]" captionTargetBox="[193,1384,185,1876]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[193,1393,179,1882]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–12. Phlogothamnus acutaedeagus Li, 2011: 1. ♂, dorsal view; 2. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 3. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus circinatus sp. nov.: 4. ♂, dorsal view; 5. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 6. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus luteoguttatus Li, 2011: 7. ♂, dorsal view; 8. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 9. ♂, face. Phlogothamnus maculiceps Ishihara, 1961: 10. ♂, dorsal view; 11. ♂, lateral view; dorsal view; 12. ♂, face." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6501257" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6501257/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
