<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A12092537CBFC7BC356FC01" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A12092537CBFC7BC356FC01" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A12092537CBFC7BC763FC6D" bold="true" box="[199,315,907,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A1209253585FC7CC273FC6D" authority="Dietrich et al. 2020" authorityName="Dietrich" authorityYear="2020" box="[649,1067,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudorugosus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A1209253585FC7CC514FC6D" box="[649,844,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">P. pseudorugosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="5E2A4B740A120925345FFC7BC273FC6D" author="Dietrich, C. H. &amp; Pham, H. T." box="[851,1067,907,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" pagination="241 - 273" refId="ref4219" refString="Dietrich, C. H., Nguyen. H. T. &amp; Pham, H. T. (2020) New genera, new species and new records of leafhoppers (Hemiptera: Cicadellidae) from Vietnam. Zootaxa, 4877 (2), 241 - 273. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4877.2.2" type="journal article" year="2020">
Dietrich 
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A12092534B9FC7CC5B4FC6D" box="[949,1004,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">et al.</emphasis>
<quantity id="FD439B600A12092534FFFC7BC273FC6D" box="[1011,1067,907,933]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1308" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" unit="in" value="2020.0">2020</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance but can be distinguished from the later by the style short and without teeth and the differently shaped connective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="72A1650E0A12092537CBFC23C73CFBD9" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="3A0436850A12092537CBFC23C73CFBD9" blockId="2.[151,1437,259,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A12092537CBFC23C716FC25" bold="true" box="[199,334,979,1005]" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName id="FDBB4D060A12092534D6FC24C211FC25" authorityName="Yao &amp; Zhang &amp; Xing" authorityYear="2022" box="[986,1097,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlogothamnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="424" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="circinatus">
<emphasis id="08CFEA970A12092534D6FC24C211FC25" box="[986,1097,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="424">circinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, referring to the crown with circular markings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
